CRUD Quiz

Use the solution to this afternoon's Property Tracker lab to answer the following questions. Please write your answers under each question, push the file to GitHub, and submit in the usual way.

MVP Questions

In our Property Tracker application:

Q1. Where are we instantiating instances of the Property class?
In property.rb

Q2. Where are we defining the SQL that enables us to save the ruby Property object into the database?
In property.sql

Q3. In console.rb, which lines modify the database?
Lines 16 - 63

Q4. Why do we not define the id of a Property object at the point we instantiate it (‘new it up’)?
Because it has not been saved to the DB therefore does not have an id no.

Q5. Where and how do we assign the id (that is generated by the database) to the ruby Property object?
In property.rb the update method adds the id no. to $5 in the array

Q6. Why do we put a guard (an if clause) on the @id attribute in the constructor?
if the id no. has not yet been generated it will return an error message

Q7. Why are some of the CRUD actions represented by instance methods, and others by class methods?
Read/Find and Delete_all are class methods, delete, create and update are not........?

Q8. What type of data structure is returned by calls to db.exec_prepared()? In the save method, how do we access the id from the returned data structure?
It is returned as a string and converted to an integer .to_i

Q9. Why do we use prepared statements when performing database operations?
Like a method it carrys out a specific operation

Extension Questions

Look at the find_by_id and find_by_address methods in the Property class.

Q10. What do they take in as their arguments?
address
Q11. What are their return values?
The property hash in an array
